quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  5,83,"And when they hear what has been sent down to the Messenger, you will see their eyes overflowing with tears on what they have recognized from the truth. They say, "Our Lord, we have come to believe. So, write us down along with those who bear witness."
  5,84,"And what excuse do we have if we do not believe in Allah and in what has come to us from the truth, while we hope that our Lord will admit us in the company of the righteous people?""
  5,85,"So, Allah has awarded them, because of what they said, gardens beneath which rivers flow, wherein they shall live forever. And that is the reward of the good in deeds."
  5,86,"And those who disbelieved and denied Our signs, they are the people of the Fire."
  5,87,"O those who believe, do not make unlawful good things that Allah has made lawful for you, and do not transgress. Verily, Allah does not like the transgressors."
  5,88,"And eat any lawful, good thing from what Allah has provided for you, and fear Allah whose believers you are."
  5,89,"Allah does not hold you accountable for what is not countable from among your oaths, but He does hold you accountable for the oath you have bound yourself with. Its expiation is to feed ten poor persons at an average of what you feed your family with, or to clothe them, or to free a slave. And whoever finds none shall fast for three days. That is expiation for your oaths when you have sworn. And take care of your oaths. That is how Allah makes His signs clear to you, so that you may be grateful."